data.title: Can I keep a single dwarf pea puffer in a 10 gallon tank or will it need a partner?
data.meta_description: Answer (1 of 2): Pea puffers do best without other pea puffers around, and they’re perfectly content being the only inhabitant in a tank (and should be, unless you keep them with other peas.)
